    'Consumer',
    'Revenue Stage',
    'Passed',
    'Sent to members via email, no interest expressed About the company: Developer of a patented wireless charging technology, trademarked FreePower, applicable to various segments including automotive, consumer products, building solutions, and power tools. The technology creates a free position charging surface that enables users to charge multiple devices placed anywhere on the pad, as opposed to single-spot wireless charging on the market today.

Pitch deck: https://docsend.com/view/rieeksxief5xnutp

Accomplishments: 
•	~$2M in non-recurring engineering contracts in 2022
•	Committed contracts with leading automotive and consumer products brands for $20M in revenue in 2023
•	150 patent applications, 30 issued patents

Team: 
Jake Slatnick, Co-founder & CEO, ASU alumni (2015)
Simon McElrea, COO, former CEO of SonicEnergy and Semblant
Jawad Ashan, President, former CFO of Axon

Round: 
Raising $35M at a $100M valuation. ~66% of funds will be used for hiring engineers, solutions architects, and project managers to execute on contracted and pipeline projects. 
Lead investor is a private equity firm in Michigan who is putting in $20M of this round. 
Aims to close by mid-December. 

Financing History: 
The company raised $12 million of seed funding from Robert Herjavec (Shark Tank), Jawad Ashan and Lori Greiner (Shark Tank) on March 8, 2021. The funding was planned for expanding the company''s reach beyond consumer device charging, into the worlds of enterprise, automotive and hospitality, as well as the development of a 2.0 version of its charging tech. Previously, A 34.64% stake in the company was acquired by Motherson Innovations and other undisclosed investors for $4 million on December 10, 2020, putting the company''s pre-money valuation at $50 million.',
