    'snapshot-company-biomorph-technologies-e9bebf35b0',
    'Biomorph Technologies',
    array['Biomorph Technologies', 'Biomorph', 'Technologies']::text[],
    'HealthTech',
    null,
    'Tracking',
    'Biomorph Technologies, LLC is an ASU startup formed by Dr. Laimonis Kelbauskas, Associate Research Professor (FSC), ASU Biodesign Center for Molecular Design and Biomimetics.  The option agreement includes technology and IP under the M22-263L^ “Peptide and Protein-Based Biomarkers for Lyme Disease diagnosis”  invention developed by Dr. Kelbauskas and his co-inventors Neal Woodbury, Visar Berisha, Joseph (Bart) Legutki, and Pradyumna Kadambi.  Biomorph plans to develop and commercialize a Lyme Disease diagnostic test developed by him and the others at ASU.  More specifically, the company describes itself as a biotechnology company focusing primarily on the development of advanced diagnostics for hard-to-detect diseases, applying next-generation, multi-modal,  multi-dimensional profiling of the patient''s molecular and phenotypic response combined with advanced machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) methods to identify and validate robust biomarkers for diagnostic, prognostic and disease progression/treatment monitoring.',
    'FY24',
    null,
