    'Convergenix Corp. was formed by Andrei Mikhailov, a current ASU Ph.D student who founded and led an artificial sapphire substrate manufacturing company for 9 years.  The evaluation license includes the technology and IP under the M20-022L "Low-capacitance nanopore sensor on insulating substrates" invention developed by Dr. Chao Wang, Assoc Professor, School of Electrical, Computer and Energy Engineering and Associate Faculty, Biodesign Center for Molecular Design and Biomimetics. The technology is a platform for sapphire-supported nanopore membranes to promote low-noise nanopore sensing (enables higher accuracy and higher speed sensing).  The company is currently engaging in customer discovery and business planning activities to determine the best path to commercialization.',
    'FY24',
    null,
