    'snapshot-company-munch-microgreens-7f29f054d4',
    'Munch Microgreens',
    array['Munch Microgreens', 'Munch', 'Microgreens']::text[],
    'AgTech',
    'Revenue Stage',
    'Passed',
    'Deadline reminder sent on 9/23   Technology focused company committed to sustainably and ethically growing microgreens indoors. Appears to have a physical store, the website allows a purchase for in-store pickup near Phoenix airport. Many growers and sellers of microgreens, especially in Arizona. Have a farm in S. Phoenix. Differentiated by focusing on the technology side of it, put seed in and use technology to have no human interaction to produce a microgreen and/or salad kit of microgreen. Traditional growers have high costs = high price point. Technology (use IoT to control production and growing of the plant and irrigation) would reduce these costs and allow the base of the salad to be microgreens, which is relatively untapped. Traditionally lightly sprinkled as a topping, not a base. The technology aspect is a very interesting idea, along with the microgreens as the bulk of the salad or food, not a light topping. Indoor facility allows them to grow all year, and harvest time is only two weeks which is way shorter than mature plants, allows for more testing. Looking to scale, would absolutely invite this company for a pitch.',
    'FY23',
    'https://www.munchmicrogreens.com/',
