  (
    'snapshot-company-omios-biologics-d801fd0d6d',
    'Omios Biologics',
    array['Omios Biologics', 'Omios', 'Biologics']::text[],
    'Life Sciences',
    'MVP',
    'Tracking',
    'Develops Immunogenic Cell Death (ICD) inducing immunotherapies, enabling sustained modifications of the tumor microenvironment and priming of the immune system against all tumor antigens present in the patient.

Omios is an ASU startup based in the San Francisco Bay area founded by Dr. Aldo Pourchet.  Omios Bio is developing Vector-induced Immunogenic Cell Death (ICD) technologies to signal cancer cells to the immune system (vaccine effect) based on ASU invention M16-201LC^ “Cell death and Oncolytic Vaccinia Virus Mutants” developed by Dr. Bertram Jacobs, Professor, School of Life Sciences and Biodesign Center for Personalized Diagnostics and several co-inventors.  The therapy, based on safe vector platforms, is systemic, versatile, and can be injected directly into patients or used in an allogeneic cell-based approach. In addition to the ASU technology and IP, Omios is developing foundational technology from the laboratory of Prof. Ed Mocarski (Stanford & Emory) who is CSO and co-founder of Omios Biologics. Co-founder and CEO Aldo Pourchet has two acquisitions: oncolytic immunotherapy T-Stealth (BeneVir - Janssen Pharmaceuticals), and AAV gene therapy RGX181 for neurodegenerative disease (REGENXBIO).',
    'FY24,FY26',
    'www.linkedin.com/company/omios-biologics',
    'aldo@omiosbio.com',
    'SkySong',
