    'Reviewed 09-22 cycle. Has since filed a provisional patent. Working with Chris Yoo.  Robust Diagnostics is developing an antibody test of 150 targets that is built upon a peptide microarray platform. Patients collect a sample at home and mail to our central processing laboratory to monitor multiple sclerosis (MS). MS affects 1M people in the US. Peptide microarrays can effectively find disease-specific markers from patient biological samples and can be used for the early diagnosis of various diseases. Monthly measurement monitors MS activity and flags a change that is reported to the neurologist for follow up. Believe it is in the right stage to invest in, and is a good company.',
